Fix AOT compatibility warnings in the following files under `/tmp/sv-11ebb9d55b96466388b8cdde93a98517/before/`. Make precise edits using the `edit` tool.

### 1. GenericOperationSource.cs
Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers]` to the generic parameter `T` of the class. The `T` is used with `ModelReaderWriter.Read(response.Content, typeof(T))` (needs PublicConstructors + NonPublicConstructors) and `Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), ...)` (needs NonPublicConstructors).

Change line 16 from:
```
    internal class GenericOperationSource<T> : IOperationSource<T>
```
to:
```
    internal class GenericOperationSource<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T> : IOperationSource<T>
```

### 2. ArmOperation.cs
Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers]` to the generic parameter `T` of the `IsResource<T>()` method. It uses `typeof(T).GetConstructor(...)` (needs NonPublicConstructors) and `Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), ...)` (needs NonPublicConstructors).

Add `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` if not already present.

Change the method signature at line 96 from:
```
        private static bool IsResource<T>() where T : notnull
```
to:
```
        private static bool IsResource<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T>() where T : notnull
```

### 3. Extensions/ArmClientBuilderExtensions.cs  
The method `AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>` calls `RegisterClientFactory` which is marked `[RequiresUnreferencedCode]` and `[RequiresDynamicCode]`. Propagate these attributes.

Add `[RequiresUnreferencedCode]` and `[RequiresDynamicCode]` to the method at line 27:

Change from:
```
        public static IAzureClientBuilder<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions> AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>(this TBuilder builder, TConfiguration configuration)
            where TBuilder : IAzureClientFactoryBuilderWithConfiguration<TConfiguration>
        {
            return builder.RegisterClientFactory<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions>(configuration);
        }
```
to:
```
        [RequiresUnreferencedCode("Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values is not supported with trimming. Use the Configuration Binder Source Generator (EnableConfigurationBindingGenerator=true) instead.")]
        [RequiresDynamicCode("Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values requires generating dynamic code at runtime, for example via Reflection.")]
        public static IAzureClientBuilder<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions> AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>(this TBuilder builder, TConfiguration configuration)
            where TBuilder : IAzureClientFactoryBuilderWithConfiguration<TConfiguration>
        {
            return builder.RegisterClientFactory<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions>(configuration);
        }
```

Make sure `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` is present at the top.

### 4. ArmEnvironment.cs
Line 80: `JsonSerializer.Serialize(this)` produces IL2026/IL3050. Replace with manual JSON using Utf8JsonWriter.

